igmine or Physostigmine (reversible AChE inhibitor), Mecamylamine (nicotinic receptor antagonist), or Atropine (mAChR antagonist) and later exposed to Soman, a strong irreversible AChE inhibitor, showed a significantly increased survival rate and overall reduced brain ACh levels compared to the control group (Harris et al., 1980).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:15:21 +0000 2026"}